92 member of the committee for more than five days unless additional days are authorized.
93 Funds necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come from funds
94 appropriated to the House of Representatives.
95 (6) Report.
96 (A) In the event the committee adopts any specific findings or recommendations that
97 include suggestions for proposed legislation, the chairperson shall file a report of the
98 same prior to the date of abolishment specified in this resolution, subject to
99 subparagraph (C) of this paragraph.
100 (B) In the event the committee adopts a report that does not include suggestions for
101 proposed legislation, the chairperson shall file the report, subject to subparagraph (C)
102 of this paragraph.
103 (C) No report shall be filed unless the same has been approved prior to the date of
104 abolishment specified in this resolution by majority vote of a quorum of the committee.
105 A report so approved shall be signed by the chairperson of the committee and filed with
106 the Clerk of the House of Representatives.
107 (D) In the absence of an approved report, the chairperson may file with the Clerk of the
108 House of Representatives a copy of the minutes of the meetings of the committee in lieu
109 thereof.
110 (7) Abolishment. The committee shall stand abolished on December 1, 2025.
